---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title={"Privacy Policy — Kingdom Bible Study"} description={"How Kingdom Bible Study handles your data: everything stays in your browser and, if you enable sync, in your own Google Drive. Nothing is evaluated, shared, or sold."}>
<Fragment slot="head-end">
<style is:inline>
  .policy-page { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 4rem; }
  .policy-page h1 { font-size: 1.7rem; margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .policy-page .policy-date { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .policy-page h2 { font-size: 1.15rem; margin: 2rem 0 0.6rem; }
  .policy-page p, .policy-page li { font-size: 0.98rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .policy-page ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .policy-page li { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
  .policy-page a { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .policy-summary {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card, 12px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card, none);
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
</Fragment>
<main>
  <div class="container policy-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="policy-date">Effective July 11, 2026 · kingdombiblestudy.com</p>

    <div class="policy-summary">
      <strong>The short version:</strong> your study data lives in your browser.
      If you connect Google Drive sync, a backup of that data is stored in
      <em>your own</em> Google Drive so you can continue on another device.
      This site has no servers, no accounts, no analytics, and no access to your
      data. Nothing is ever evaluated, shared, or sold — by anyone, for anything.
    </div>

    <h2>What this site stores, and where</h2>
    <p>
      Kingdom Bible Study is a personal Bible study application. Everything you
      create while using it — reading progress and plans, notes and highlights,
      bookmarks, prayer journal entries, gratitude and reflection entries,
      scripture memory, worship log, discipline history, and site preferences —
      is stored <strong>locally in your browser</strong> (localStorage). By
      default it never leaves your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Google Drive sync (optional)</h2>
    <p>
      If you choose to connect Google Drive in <a href="/settings/">Settings →
      Sync &amp; Backup</a>, the site stores a single backup file of the data
      listed above in the <strong>private application-data area of your own
      Google Drive</strong>, and retrieves it to bring another device up to
      date. That is the sync feature's only purpose:
      <strong>cross-device continuation of your own progress, prayers, notes,
      and study data</strong>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>The backup travels <strong>directly from your browser to Google</strong>.
        This site is statically hosted and has no servers of its own — there is
        no intermediary that could see, copy, or retain your data.</li>
      <li>The site requests only the <code>drive.appdata</code> permission: a
        hidden app-specific area of your Drive. It <strong>cannot</strong> see,
        read, or touch any of your other Drive files.</li>
      <li>The site operator has <strong>no access</strong> to your Google
        account, your Drive, or your backups.</li>
      <li>Your data is <strong>never evaluated, analyzed, profiled, shared,
        rented, or sold</strong>. There is no advertising and no analytics.</li>
      <li>Kingdom Bible Study's use of information received from Google APIs
        adheres to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy">Google
        API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use
        requirements.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your controls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Disconnect</strong> at any time in Settings → Sync &amp; Backup
        — the site loses all access to your Drive immediately.</li>
      <li><strong>Revoke access</strong> from Google's side at
        <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Delete the backup</strong> in Google Drive: Settings (in Drive)
        → Manage apps → Kingdom Bible Study → delete hidden app data.</li>
      <li><strong>Delete local data</strong> by clearing this site's storage in
        your browser settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p>
      This site sets no tracking cookies and runs no analytics. Browser storage
      is used solely to make the app itself work (your data and preferences,
      plus offline caching of scripture and app files by the service worker).
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the new version will be posted at this address
      with an updated effective date. Questions can be raised on the
      <a href="https://github.com/seriousd6/Seriousd6.github.io">project's
      GitHub repository</a>.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/terms/">Terms of Service →</a></p>
  </div>
</main>
</Base>
